        "content": "<p>I am trying to state the theorem that the rings 2ℤ and 3ℤ are not isomorphic. However I am not sure which type to use to represent the quotient set on ℤ given by ℤMod2 and ℤMod3. </p>\n<p>Any ideas appreciated, I have a feeling that its something to do with the Quotient type perhaps. </p>\n<p>Here is my attempt so far which fails to typecheck. </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">zmod2_not_isomorphic_to_zmod3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IsEmpty</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">((</span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⧸</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ZMod</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≃+*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⧸</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ZMod</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I get <code>failed to synthesize HasQuotient ℤ Type</code> as an error. Is this because ℤ needs to be replaced with the ring of ℤ maybe.</p>",
        "id": 562253549,
        "sender_full_name": "Tom",
        "timestamp": 1765041137
    },
    {
